The Butane Tank Blending is a batch-type process based on seasonal RVP adjustments. Butane is received by truck (transports) and piped directly to and injected into the gasoline recirculation line associated with the product tank to be blended. Process safety controls include an emergency shutoff valve with multiple, isolation valves, and a fusible element along with a "Smart-Hose", low emission hose coupler, and thermal/hydrostatic pressure reliefs. Access to the Brecksville LP Terminal is restricted to authorized employees, management personnel and authorized contractors/visitors.

B. GENERAL ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION PROGRAM AND CHEMICAL-SPECIFIC PREVENTION MEASURES

The Brecksville LP Terminal accidental release prevention programs and emergency planning/response programs help Marathon effectively manage the hazards posed by the regulated substances to the Terminal employees, surrounding public, and environment. The covered process is regulated by the EPA RMP regulation 40 CFR Part 68, OSHA Process Safety Management standard 29 CFR 1910.119, as well as the Ohio EPA (Ohio Administrative Code Rule 3745-104.) The following accident prevention program elements are in place at the Brecksville LP Terminal:

1) Employee Participation;
2) Process Safety Information;
3) Process Hazard Analysis (PHA);
4) Operating Procedures;
5) Training;
6) Contractors;
7) Pre-startup Safety Review;
8) Mechanical Integrity with Preventive Maintenance/Inspection/Testing;
